-- Uganda Arrests 20 Somalians Over Bomb Attacks in Kampala, New Vision Says
-- Fred Ojambo
-- 2010-07-20T04:58:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/uganda-arrests-20-somalians-over-bomb-attacks-new-vision-newspaper-says.html

          
          
             Uganda has arrested at least 20
Somalians after bomb attacks in Kampala, the countryâ€™s capital,
left 74 people dead on July 11, the New Vision reported, citing
unidentified security officials.  
 The arrests were made in different parts of the country and
bring the total number of arrest since the attack to at least
40, including 7 Pakistani citizens, the Kampala-based newspaper
reported.  
